text: David Ickringill (1930–2012), was a male wrestler who competed for England. ==Wrestling career== He represented England in the -68kg division at the 1950 British Empire Games in Auckland, New Zealand. Eight years later he represented England in the -74kg division at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. ==Personal life== During the Games in 1950 he lived at Well Street, Keighley and was a decorator by trade. ==References== Category:1930 births Category:2012 deaths Category:English male wrestlers Category:Wrestlers at the 1950 British Empire Games Category:Wrestlers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games
